    {
      "question": "A Certified Fraud Examiner is analyzing large datasets of expense reimbursement claims using data analytics software. Which of the following techniques would be MOST effective for identifying potential duplicate payment fraud schemes?",
      "options": [
        "Performing stratification analysis to group transactions by dollar amount ranges",
        "Using fuzzy matching algorithms to compare vendor names, invoice numbers, dates, and amounts across all records",
        "Conducting trend analysis to identify seasonal variations in reimbursement patterns",
        "Applying regression analysis to predict expected reimbursement amounts based on employee department"
      ],
      "correct_answer": 1,
      "explanation": "Fuzzy matching algorithms are specifically designed to identify potential duplicates by comparing multiple fields (vendor names, invoice numbers, dates, amounts) even when there are slight variations in how the data is entered. This technique is highly effective for detecting duplicate payment fraud where perpetrators may slightly alter information to avoid detection. Stratification groups data by ranges but doesn't identify duplicates. Trend analysis identifies patterns over time but not duplicates. Regression analysis predicts expected values but doesn't specifically target duplicate payments.",
